In her remarks to the National Jewish Leaders Assembly, National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice expressed America's unwavering support for Israel's right to self-defense. She emphasized the shared belief that every person is created equal and reaffirmed the commitment to protect innocent lives on both sides of the conflict. Rice also acknowledged the efforts of Secretary Kerry and the United States' strong support for Israel's security, including the funding of the Iron Dome anti-rocket system. She highlighted the need to fight for Israel's legitimacy and condemned anti-Semitism and unfair treatment of Israel at the United Nations. Rice also discussed the ongoing negotiations with Iran and the determination to prevent the country from acquiring a nuclear weapon. She concluded by emphasizing the importance of hope, service, and working together to achieve security and peace.